MultiClass classification is the task of assigning data points to more than two predefined categories. It's like sorting items into multiple bins, 
but instead of just two (like "yes" or "no"), you have several distinct categories.

More info to follow link is here -> https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/machine-learning/tutorials/github-issue-classification

Prepare your data
Transform the data
Train the model
Evaluate the model
Predict with the trained model
Deploy and Predict with a loaded model

